{
  "texts": [
    "Sometimes, LLMs can 'hallucinate', generating factually incorrect contents [15].",
    "Early research efforts focused on improving the training data quality, emphasizing the importance of curated datasets that minimize the presence of erroneous or biased information [16].",
    "Enhanced preprocessing techniques were developed to filter out unreliable sources, thereby improving the overall accuracy of LLMs [17].",
    "Another approach involved fine-tuning LLMs on domain-specific data, which helped in aligning LLMs' outputs with factual information pertinent to particular fields [18].",
    "Fine-tuning also allowed models to leverage more accurate and relevant data, reducing the chances of generating misleading content [19]."
  ]
}